HEADWORD: Monocarpellary
<hw>Mon`o*car"pel*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + <ets>carpellary</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Consisting of a single carpel, as the fruit of the pea, cherry, and
almond.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

